	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=65101><span id=Scholar>Drienne, Guardian of the Glade</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>291 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.80]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>You're mostly right.&nbsp;&nbsp;The damage bonus is different, whether you're using 1handers or 2handers (bows have no damage bonus, even though there's one listed on the item).  1handers have a specific bonus based solely on level.  Whether you have a revultant whip (5/14) or a wurmslayer (25/40), the damage bonus is the same.  On 2handers, the damage bonus is determined by two factors: level and delay.  At any given level, weapons with a higher delay have a higher damage bonus.<br><br>Now, for how a damage bonus actually works.  A weapon is swung, if it's a hit, the damage is applied.  After the initial damage is calculated, the damage bonus is added.  So, for example, let's say you took two swings of this weapon, and connected both times.  The damage is calculated as 100 for the first hit, and 1 for the second hit.  Add 40 to each, and you get 140 and 41.  That's how the damage bonus works.  The damage bonus is *always* added, so long as the weapon connects, and it's always the same amount.  Damage bonuses work the same for 1handers as they do for 2handers.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Dec  5 01:04:50 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=76285 target=akztarg>Drienne Gardairne</a> -- 65 Ranger<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=316502 target=akztarg>Xide Kyck</a> -- 65 Necromancer<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=725442 target=akztarg>Hwel Jung</a> -- 65 Rogue</td></tr>
